Package: rstudio.clipboard.path
Title: RStudio Add-in — Set Working Directory from Clipboard Path
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: person("HTang", email = "tang.heng@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: RStudio add-in (Windows, macOS, Linux): read a directory or file
    path from the system clipboard, set the session working directory and Files
    pane, and open the file in the editor when it uses a common R-related
    extension. Clipboard access uses the 'clipr' package; on Linux you may need
    xclip, xsel, or wl-clipboard.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Imports:
    clipr (>= 0.4),
    rstudioapi (>= 0.13)
Suggests:
    later
